: 20px 0;"&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;table width="580"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/ih7zzmZ9u.rQ/v0/-1x-1.jpg" alt="Demonstrators clash with riot police during a protest demanding the resignation of Bolivian President Rodrigo Paz, in La Paz, on May 18, 2026. Bolivians have taken to the streets for the past two weeks, blocking roads into La Paz and disrupting deliveries of food, medicine and other goods to the seat of government, while demanding higher wages, economic relief and the resignation of centre-right President Rodrigo Paz amid a severe economic crisis. (Photo by AIZAR RALDES &amp;amp;#x2F; AFP via Getty Images) Photographer: AIZAR RALDES&amp;amp;#x2F;AFP" width="580"/&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;div style="display:none"&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;img alt="2026 年 5 月 18 日，在拉巴斯，示威者在要求玻利维亚总统罗德里戈·帕斯辞职的抗议活动中与防暴警察发生冲突。过去两周，玻利维亚人走上街头，封锁通往拉巴斯的道路，扰乱向政府所在地运送食品、药品和其他货物，同时要求提高工资、经济救济，并在严重的经济危机中要求中右翼总统罗德里戈·帕斯辞职。 （AIZAR RALDES＆#x2F;法新社通过盖蒂图片社拍摄）摄影师：AIZAR RALDES＆#x2F;法新社" src="https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/ih7zzmZ9u.rQ/v0/-1x-1.jpg" style="width: 100%; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;" /&gt;&lt;!--[if mso]&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;div style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.4;"&gt; 5 月 18 日，拉巴斯发生抗议活动。&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;div style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.4; font-style: italic;"&gt;摄影师：Aizar Raldes/法新社/盖蒂图片社&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 24px; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 16px;"&gt;特朗普即将在 80 岁生日前进行体检，&lt;/strong&gt;这将加强自十多年前他首次竞选美国最高职位以来一直围绕着他的&lt;a href="https://links.message.bloomberg.com/a/sc/SmdArO7yQUlD988CQHGJC9PurfZ_LPU48EXsPuDobf6iivnjrt9kMpGRldSj6RS9a3wClIpJKKdoC38kEKGhB9oDzeGGcvTfMxiA0l3hL_HoPuJq75puDkESk6OwzXWW9vjjHhbHjPwrImOj7wSM77r1VQjsaCkhJTgI7cgQhQgXXu6apbXV1jEI6H11G7EZPh5HB2861ZGnaEcT-FolobpbGgVpD5sr2yQQVPPAGqYBiVDgQyAyxqKjRExjpXLSlipZE8OYvlYpcDU1_cspa1upV1-t_darCO4czMIOTBe-u